name: Name of act
description: 50 Words

name: Joel Sulman
description: Joel Sulman is described as “being from the Old School” (Jamie Horne, Border Mail). His style of blues is “as accessible as it is bona-fide”. His lyrics come from experiences, His music from the heart. With an engaging and powerful rasp that helps add a legitimate storytelling quality to his craft, Joel exits the stage with a crowd engaged yet breathless.

name: Candice McLeod
description: Nomadic songstress Candice McLeod, originally from south-east Queensland, has her travelling shoes permanently on these days.  Over the past three years, this young creative soul has lived a gypsy life on the road, touring Australia extensively with her modern-folk tunes. She launched her debut EP, ‘Live in Bruthen’, earlier this year at the Bruthen Blues & Arts Festival, Victoria.

name: The Kissin Cousins
description: Live and stomping, the kissin Cousins hail from Northeast Victorian and add a fresh, youthful Australian sound to traditional bluegrass and old time music. The cousins move between frantic Scruggs style banjo and volcanic mandolin to sweet, melodic ballads. The cousins have been featured at bluegrass festivals all over Australia and bring to their audience a show like no other!

name: Gorani
description: GORANI, meaning "Mountain Men",  an  11 voice male vocal group, has been meeting every Tuesday night since 1992 specialising in Bulgarian songs initially, but mainly singing Georgian songs in recent years. It has travelled to Georgia as a performing group six times and has appeared on national TV and radio in Georgia, Bulgaria and Australia.

name: The Bon Scotts
description: “With their trademark satire, charm, and penchant for nonstop folk pop, Modern Capitalism Gets Things Done, examines lost love, seedy friendships, the free market and summers golden promise. Continuing to push the boundaries of folk, the album uses accordion, violin, acoustic guitars, banjo, harmonica, cello, tuba, and all kinds of percussive oddities, alongside analogue synths, programmed drums, vocoders and a small symphony”

name: Gordie Tentrees
description: International touring award winning Canadian Gordie Tentrees has released 6 albums performing over 200 concerts in 11 countries each year. Performing with him is world class multi-insturmentalist Jaxon Haldane "Sounding like a young John Prine" NO DEPRESSION

name: Tom Richardson
description: After a whirlwind couple of years living and touring throughout Canada, Europe and Indonesia, Tom Richardson returns home to Australia with a brand new CD, inspiring one-man live looping show and infectious demeanour.  An adventurous yet humble artist, appreciating the freedom of travel, exploration and the privilege of forging relationships with listeners and cultures around the world.

name: Yoga Loves Music
description: YLM is an exciting workshop collaboration between Canadian-born yoga instructor, Kimberly Erin, and internationally renowned Australian singer-songwriter, Tom Richardson. Flow with your breath in an uplifting yoga practice that consciously merges live music with body, mind and heart.

name: Scott Cook
description: A roots balladeer with a rare personal warmth, Canada's Scott Cook has managed to distil the stories collected over years of near-incessant touring across Canada, the USA, Europe, Asia, and Australia into straight-talking, keenly observant verse.  He's currently touring in support of his fifth DIY release, Go Long.  All the hard miles notwithstanding, he still believes that songs can change your life, and your life can change the world.

name: The Jessica Stuart Few
description: This Canadian folk-jazz power-trio has one of the freshest sounds on the international indie music scene. Innovative songwriting, stunning 3-part harmonies, and a unique take on the Japanese koto (13-stringed harp) aside, the trio have an undeniably charismatic onstage presence, propelling audiences out of their seats and onto their feet at festivals worldwide.

name: The Eastern
description: The Eastern are a string band that roars like a punk band, swings like a gospel band, drinks like a country band, works like a bar band, hopes like folk singers, and want to slow dance and stand on tables all at the same time.

name: Black Market Tune
description: Austrian World Music award recipients, Black Market Tune are An outstanding example of musicians networking across Europe and the profound impact of the Celtic Folk genre.  With many strands of Ethno, American and European folk Black Market Tune presents a powerful musical tapestry.  Their first recording "Nightfire' appeared in 2013 and this tour will see the launch of their second CD.

name: Sheila Kay Adams
description: SHEILA KAY ADAMS is an American ballad singer, banjo player, writer and story teller from North Carolina. For seven generations, her family has maintained the tradition of passing down the English, Scottish, and Irish ballads. Adams was awarded a National Heritage Fellowship in 2013, and received the North Carolina Heritage Award 2015. Her innovating tunes with her signature drop-thumb style banjo skills has won her numerous awards.

name: The Northern Folk
description: The Northern Folk are a 9-piece alternative ensemble from Albury, with a merging of folk/blues/funk/rock. Focusing on original songs with group vocal sections, murky bass lines, and big catchy horn hooks, the Folk mix high-energy moments with stripped back acoustic sound, targeted at all demographics and groovers.

name: Fred Smith & Liz Frencham
description: Fred Smith’s remarkable career as songwriter and war zone diplomat was the subject of a recent Australian Story documentary. He returns to Yack with Liz Frencham to play songs from their back catalogue and his new album Home, the follow up to his acclaimed 2011 release, Dust of Uruzgan.

name: Julz Evans
description: Julz Evans' music is honest, earthy and thoughtfully composed. It is with the full band (including cellist Laura Weedy) that her music is truly brought to life. The release of her 14-track album "Until It Hurts And Then Some" will be supported with a national tour this November.

name: Joel Havea
description: Joel Havea is a Tongan born, Melbourne raised songwriter, who has spent the last 6 years living in Hamburg, Germany. In between constant touring around Europe & Australia, he has independently released an album & EP and is currently working on his next album in a trio formation with drums and bass.

name: Steve Tyson
description: GREEN SIDE UP, an album of war, love, murder and humour, is the second album of eclectic folk songs from Byron Bay based singer-songwriter Steve Tyson, resonating strongly with critics who honoured it with 4 star reviews in the national music press.

name: The Raes
description: Originally hailing from Yackandandah, The Raes have been singing together for 15 years. This sister duo performs a range of styles, including toe-tapping country, indie and traditional folk. With their soaring vocals and rich harmonies, Anna and Eliza will warm you from the inside out.

name: Lulu & the Paige-Turners
description: Lulu Paige-Turner invigorates a theatrical performance inspired by the performances of bands such as gypsy-cabaret group Rapscallion and punk-cabaret duo The Dresden Dolls. With her band, Lulu and the Paige-Turners blend contemporary folk sounds, sweet pop melodies and caberat-esque rhythm. Their arresting live performances have mesmerised audiences.

name: The Hannafords
description: Described by Rhythms magazine as "Australian dirt music in its purest form" (July 13), The Hannafords have a unique and distinctive flavour to their well-crafted original songs. Little bit Celtic, little bit bluegrass, with a strong folk edge, sometimes funny, sometimes serious, always enjoyable - their stories are delivered with honesty and skill.

name: Lucy Wise & Stephen Taberner
description: Lucy’s best known as the dreamvoiced ukelele wielding songmaker from a family band from Margaret River WA, Stephen as double bass playing crooner and creator of the Spooky Men’s Chorale. Together, they explore a whole bunch of highly necessary conversations: between the bass and the uke, between the resonance and the groove, between verbal nuance and sweet cadence, between grand stupidity and grace.

name: The East Pointers
description: Ontario guitarist Jake Charron and 7th generation PEI musicians Tim (fiddle) and Koady Chaisson (banjo) make traditional music seem ridiculously hip.  An adrenalized, roof-rattling, performance monster, the trio’s excellent new release ‘Secret Victory’, penned mostly in Australia in early 2015, features beautiful songs and a series of free-wheeling, feisty instrumental jigs, stomps and reels.

name: Whiteline
description: For almost two decades, this trio has blended their idividual musical influences into a unique Australian Folk Rock style, creating intimate balads about rural Australia.  Take a journey with them through Australia’s past and present, and be left with a warm feeling of strength, resilience and contentment, that is truly Australian.

name: Frank Yamma
description: The man Everbody's Talking about in the world music scene globally is Indigenous soulster Frank Yamma. Having spent the Australian Winter touring across North America, Europe and UK with shows in Canada, Latvia, Wales, Ireland, England, Scotland and Switzerland, Frank Yamma continues to capture the hearts and emotions of all who see him perform.

name: Mick Thomas
description: Mick Thomas has been a staple of Melbourne’s music scene for well over 25 years. Raconteur, troubadour, balladeer and poet, Mick Thomas is best known as the Blundstone-wearing song master of pub-rock icons Weddings Parties Anything. His band The Roving Commission features Squeezebox Wally on Piano Accordion and a rotating schedule of talented performers to keep the party alive.

name: Tooze & Bruce
description: Melbourne folk pop duo Tooze & Bruce are two singer songwriters who have been hanging out non stop all year. Their lyrics jump around from straight up pop to philosophical voyages as the songs go by. But above all, their harmonies are making peoples ears prick up all over town as Luke Tooze & Simon Bruce get ever so close to a debut single release. (December 1st 2015) Beat Magazine.

name: Broads
description: BROADS is the musical partnership of Kelly Day and Jane Hendry. With years of singing together in vocal vintage pop group The Nymphs (as seen on Spicks & Specks, RocKwiz), Kel and Jane have developed a harmonic symbiosis that is evident in their luscious harmonies and the way they interact during their live shows, often sharing a knowing smile throughout their set.

name: Jali Buba Kuyateh
description: A master of traditional kora tunes, Jali Buba has applied his kora to the Afro Manding styles, soukous of Mali and Guinee Conakry, the mbalah, reggae, salsa, jazz and the blues. Jali has appeared at festivals around Australia including WOMADelaide, The Melbourne International Festival, Woodford and Port Fairy Folk Festivals, to name a few.

name: Fat Yahoozah
description: What's a Fat Yahoozah? Mash together a bunch of music genres everywhere from afrobeat to balkan, to mariachi and klezmer. Throw in some boogaloo and ska, fun and slightly off-kilter vocals plus epic improvised solos, and hey presto!

name: Sheehan Smith & Sheehan
description: Marni Mark & Dave play  traditional songs in a blues or country style, some dating back to the 1800s, or classics penned by Robert Johnson and Woody Guthrie. Originals are stylistically in keeping and are co-written/arranged by all members. Audiences love the sparkle, variety & humour of this act
